cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of learning from untrusted batches, which is a problem in machine learning. The use of sum-of-squares algorithms and the incorporation of prior knowledge about the shape of the distribution suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with combinatorial constraints, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of prior knowledge about the shape of the distribution suggests that the paper may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
